# AKOS Quality Fabric

Use this rule whenever authoring, reviewing, or shipping a **quality-bound artifact** in this workspace. Codifies operator decision **D-IH-86-AU** (operator-ratified the 5-axis composition architecture, 2026-05-20). Mechanical companion to the meta-canonical [`HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the canonical. This rule names the mechanical bar that future agents and operators inherit by default when handling any artifact whose quality bar is non-trivial.

## What counts as a "quality-bound artifact"

An artifact is quality-bound — and therefore in scope for this rule — when **at least one** of:

- It carries an `audience:` frontmatter tag that resolves to any class other than (or in addition to) J-OP / J-AIC.
- It is a closure UAT report or any other report that gates an INITIATIVE_REGISTRY status flip.
- It is rendered for external delivery (PDF / Web / ERP / Mail / Slide / Broadcast per [`akos-external-render-discipline.mdc`](akos-external-render-discipline.mdc) RULE 1).
- It is a brand-touching surface (deck slide body, dossier prose, web page, email body, dashboard chrome, identity asset).
- It is shipped to a sibling repository (`hlk-erp`, `boilerplate`, `kirbe-platform`) and triggers a deploy.
- It is a Quality-Fabric-specialty canonical (UAT_DISCIPLINE, UX_DISCIPLINE, channel-doctrines) or a cursor rule that materialises a specialty compose() function.

Artifacts NOT in scope: code-only refactors with no human-facing surface; internal scratchpad entries; agent self-checkpoints; debugging notes; test fixtures; ephemeral one-off scripts.

## RULE 1 — Five-axis resolution discipline (binding)

Every quality-bound artifact's frontmatter (or its parent initiative's master-roadmap frontmatter, when the artifact lives inside an initiative folder) **must** carry resolvable values for the five axes:

1. **Audience axis.** `audience:` tag (single value or `;`-separated list). FK-resolves against [`AUDIENCE_REGISTRY.csv`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/dimensions/AUDIENCE_REGISTRY.csv). Multi-audience tags resolve to the **strictest** constraint per downstream axis.
2. **Channel axis.** `channel:` tag (optional today; advisory per [`akos-external-render-discipline.mdc`](akos-external-render-discipline.mdc) RULE 7). When present, FK-resolves against [`CHANNEL_TOUCHPOINT_REGISTRY.csv`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/dimensions/CHANNEL_TOUCHPOINT_REGISTRY.csv). When absent, the bar derives audience-only and channel-side constraints fall back to the audience-class default.
3. **Scenario axis.** `scenario:` tag (optional today). When present, FK-resolves against [`PERSONA_SCENARIO_REGISTRY.csv`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/Resonance/canonicals/dimensions/PERSONA_SCENARIO_REGISTRY.csv). When absent, scenario falls back to the artifact's parent-initiative scope description.
4. **Brand axis.** Always non-null. The variable is the **register** (CORPINT-internal vs translated-external per [`akos-brand-baseline-reality.mdc`](akos-brand-baseline-reality.mdc)).
5. **Governance axis.** Always non-null. Determined by the artifact's asset class per [`PRECEDENCE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/PRECEDENCE.md) + the cursor rules that scope it.

When any of axes 1-3 is unresolvable, the artifact is **under-specified**. Under-specified artifacts cannot reach a PASS verdict in their UAT/UX bar — the agent must either resolve the axis (via inline-ratify per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc)) or carry the under-specification flag explicitly in `notes:` frontmatter with a closure-target.

## RULE 2 — Multiplicative-AND composition (binding)

The five axes compose **multiplicatively**: every constraint from every axis must be satisfied. Composition is **not** additive (no axis dominates) and **not** sequential (no last-axis-wins). When two axes appear to conflict, BOTH constraints apply. Genuine conflicts surface as inline-ratify gates per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc) — the agent does not silently pick one axis.

This rule operationalises the doctrine in [`HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md) §3 (the load-bearing claim of the fabric) by binding it to artifact authoring practice.

## RULE 3 — Closure UAT for sibling-repo work must include deploy-class verification (binding)

When a closure UAT report's parent initiative ships work to a sibling repository (`hlk-erp`, `boilerplate`, `kirbe-platform`, or any other repo registered in [`REPOSITORY_REGISTRY.csv`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/REPOSITORY_REGISTRY.csv)) AND that work triggers a deploy, the closure UAT report **must** include a deploy-class verification section (per [`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md) §3.7).

Minimum content:

- Deploy ID + source sha + state (READY / ERROR / BUILDING) verified via vendor MCP.
- For Vercel deploys: `user-vercel` MCP `get_deployment` call output evidence.
- For Render deploys: equivalent Render service-status check.
- If state is ERROR and was recovered, both the ERROR and READY phases are recorded with the hotfix lineage between them.
- A reproducible MCP-call command future readers can re-run.

**Why this is binding.** The Vercel `dpl_6uNfwjKVUNwqqd2MZ65vySkvd834` regression on 2026-05-20 (server-only-import poisoning client bundle; production-broken for ~14 hours before operator caught it) demonstrated that local `tsc` PASS does not imply vendor-side build PASS. Build-context-class regressions are routinely caught only at vendor-MCP verification time. This rule's existence ensures that gap is closed mechanically.

## RULE 4 — Brand-class UAT must reference Figma source-of-truth when one exists (binding when applicable)

When a brand-class UAT (per [`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md) §3.2) exercises a surface that has a corresponding entry in [`FIGMA_FILES_REGISTRY.csv`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/Brand/canonicals/dimensions/FIGMA_FILES_REGISTRY.csv), the UAT report's findings table **must** include a row checking divergence against the Figma source-of-truth at the documented breakpoint.

When the surface does **not** have a Figma source-of-truth, the rule no-ops — but the agent should consider whether minting one is appropriate (forward-charter scope; not blocking).

## RULE 5 — External-audience artifacts must satisfy compose_render() before send (binding)

For any artifact tagged `audience:` with one or more external classes (J-IN, J-CU, J-PT, J-AD, J-ENISA, J-RC, J-CO), the render-class UAT bar in [`akos-external-render-discipline.mdc`](akos-external-render-discipline.mdc) RULE 4 + RULE 6 applies. The compose_render() output (which 6-surface format is required, what manifest sidecar is required, what render-pending tracker entry is needed if render parity is not yet reached) must be explicitly addressed in the artifact's UAT report or in its parent initiative closure UAT.

This rule is the umbrella that binds the existing render-discipline rule to the broader Quality Fabric architecture.

## RULE 6 — Inline-ratify when an axis is contested (binding)

When two axes' constraints appear to conflict on a specific decision (e.g., audience demands brevity but governance demands completeness; brand demands warmth but channel demands transactional terseness), the agent surfaces an inline-ratify gate per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc) before drafting the conflicting prose.

Pattern: in the `AskQuestion` body, name the two conflicting axes + their respective constraints + the proposed reconciliation options + a recommended default. The operator's ratification embeds in the artifact's `linked_decisions:` frontmatter.

This rule operationalises the multi-axis composition from RULE 2 in agent practice.

## RULE 7 — Specialty canonicals inherit the fabric (advisory)

When authoring a new specialty canonical that materialises a compose() function for a domain (the existing precedents are UAT_DISCIPLINE.md + UX_DISCIPLINE.md forward-charter + akos-external-render-discipline.mdc), the canonical:

1. **Cross-references** [`HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md) as parent meta-doctrine.
2. **Names its compose() function explicitly** (e.g., `compose_UAT(audience, channel, scenario, brand, governance) → 7-class UAT shape`).
3. **Lands at `status: charter`** if not yet exercised by a real worked example; promotes to `status: active` per the Quality Fabric §10 promotion criteria.
4. **Cites internal precedents** (existing UAT reports, existing render-trail manifests, existing brand-canon edits) for each construct it introduces.
5. **Cites at least one external research source** when the framing is novel (per [`akos-applied-research-discipline.mdc`](akos-applied-research-discipline.mdc) RULE 2).

## When this rule does NOT apply

- One-off scripts under `scripts/` that are not registered in `process_list.csv`.
- Internal helper modules inside `akos/` (no human-facing surface).
- Test fixtures + ephemeral debugging artifacts.
- Pre-2026-05-20 closure UAT reports (no retroactive backfill required; new bar applies forward-only per `akos-planning-traceability.mdc` UAT quality bar §migration posture).
- Operator-internal scratchwork (scratchpads + agent self-checkpoints + debugging notes).

## Self-discipline rules for agents

When generating prose under this rule's globs:

1. **Resolve the 5 axes BEFORE drafting.** Skipping the resolution and reverse-engineering the bar after-the-fact is the most common failure mode and produces brand drift + audience-mismatch + missing deploy-verification.
2. **Cite the resolved axes inline in frontmatter.** `audience:`, `channel:` (when known), `scenario:` (when known), `linked_decisions:` (governance axis), brand-register-implicit-via-content. Absence of these tags is a quality signal.
3. **Compose, don't substitute.** Two axes' constraints both apply. When they conflict, surface as inline-ratify (RULE 6).
4. **Read the per-axis doctrine before drafting.** Do not infer brand voice from prior outputs; read [`BRAND_DO_DONT.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Marketing/Brand/canonicals/BRAND_DO_DONT.md). Do not infer channel norms from intuition; read the per-channel doctrine (when minted) or call out the gap in `notes:`.
5. **Refuse under-specified artifacts.** When asked to produce an artifact whose audience or channel cannot be resolved, refuse or surface as inline-ratify before proceeding.

